{"questionId":"6274","questionHtml":"<p>Calculate the Reynolds number for the water flow.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><em>R</em> =&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{59.4 \\times 0.6 \\times 1 \\times {{10}^3}}}{{1.31 \\times {{10}^{ - 3}}}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>59.4</mn>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mn>0.6</mn>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mn>1</mn>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mrow>\n            <mn>10</mn>\n          </mrow>\n          <mn>3</mn>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>1.31</mn>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mrow>\n            <mn>10</mn>\n          </mrow>\n          <mrow>\n            <mo>−</mo>\n            <mn>3</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span> = 2.72&nbsp;× 10<sup>7</sup></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em>Accept use of radius 0.3 m giving value 1.36 × 10</em><sup><em>7</em></sup><em>.</em></p>\n<p><strong><em>[1 mark]</em></strong></p>","meta":{"questionId":"6274","referenceCode":"18M.3.HL.TZ1.10c.i","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"Calculate the Reynolds number for the water flow.","paper":"3","level":"HL","questionNumber":"c.i","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Option B: Engineering physics","Option B: Engineering physics","Option B: Engineering physics (Additional higher level option topics)","B.3 – Fluids and fluid dynamics (HL only)","Option B: Engineering physics","Option B: Engineering physics (Additional higher level option topics)"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}